						<h1>ECYSAP</h1>
						<h2>European Cyber Situational <br>Awareness Platform</h2>
						<p><strong>The main objective of the ECYSAP</strong> project is to develop and implement of innovative theoretical foundations, methods, research prototypes
and their integration towards providing a European operational platform for enabling real-time Cyber Situational Awareness with rapid
							response defensive capabilities and decision-making support for military end-users.<br>
						  <br>
						</p>
					  <p>An integrated and modular <strong>Cyber Situational Awareness (CSA)</strong>A picture for National/European security purposes and military expeditionary
operations will be developed, which shall become a real time defensive system capable of cyber response, automated and deployable in
the same area of operations (National/European) interconnected between envisaged and identified intelligent nodes.</p>
						
				</div>
					
 <p></p>
 <br><br>

			</div>
				
		</div>
			
			<h2 class="single_text_widget_inner">ECYSAP Highlights</h2>
			
			<p><strong>1. ECYSAP</strong> will design, implement and validate a toolset of analytical enablers to support risk identification, assessment and its propagation estimation at both CIS and mission levels. <br>
		    These capabilities shall also support the activities engaged in reactive/proactive responses, including the identification, selection, planning and enforcement of CoAs at CIS/Mission level. Particular attention must be paid to facilitate the projection based on simulations and predictions of the operational environment and CoAs at different time horizons (short-term, mid-term, high-term scopes). <br>
		    This will facilitate the decision of anticipatory responses as actions drivenby expectations of future events, and the evolution of the propagation and replicas of discovered threats.</p>
			<br>			
			
			<p><strong>2. ECYSAP</strong> will design, develop and validate capabilities facilitating information sharing and reporting at technical or mission level and between both. They will allow to share threat information and impacts to missions and offer user-friendly ways to access relevant and clear information. <br>
This will enable stakeholders to share all kinds of information (incidents, threats, risks, impacts, analysis...) and to make decisions in a collaborative and synchronized way according to predefined workflows. These capacities will rely on standardized descriptors and models to enable interoperability. Resilience of communication means is a major concern. It will be managed by the integration of audit and self-protection functions and by hardening the ECYSAP system. <br>
Any issue related to the ECYSAP system will be reported the same way other cyber security issues will. All components prototyped thorough will embrace the security and privacy by design principles, which evolution will be documented aiming on facilitating future certification. </p><br>
			
			<p><strong>3. ECYSAP</strong> platform and its subcomponents abilities for operating with effectiveness in real operational domain will be corroborated by exhaustive validation tests and demonstrations on real use cases directly supported by compromised EU Member States. The validation activities will be conducted on virtual labs, testbeds, including white/grey/black box scenarios against both automated adversarial actions and read teams. 
			<br>
			
			<p><strong>4. The ECYSAP project</strong>, in addition to being carried out in accordance with the most well-known project management methodologies, will be carried out with the aim of creating an intrinsically secure platform. To this end, a secure by design approach will be adopted from platform's requirements definition phase, integrating in the functional solution’s requirements non-functional security requirements. This approach therefore brings the safety requirements in the design and development phase of each component of the platform. Also, the test phase of the platform will include the verification of the robustness and safety requirements. <br>
The "secure by design" methodology to be used during the project lifecycle will be defined by the consortium on the basis of the market best practices and on the experiences of each partner. </p><br>
